  "texts": [
    "Companies might overstate their commitment to socially or environmentally responsible behavior.",
    "For example, they might only comply with their principles on paper, without making substantive changes.",
    "This practice is called \"ethics washing\" [25,151,171] or \"bluewashing\" [56] analog to \"greenwashing\" [50].",
    "For an overview of the different concepts, see [150].",
    "Meta's Oversight Board has already been accused of ethics washing (at least implicitly)."
  ],
